# Dong Build Configuration - Android
# Copy this file to build.env and adjust paths for your system
#
# Android cross-compilation requires:
# 1. Android NDK installed
# 2. Target architecture specified in zig build command
#
# Example build commands:
#   zig build -Dtarget=aarch64-linux-android         # ARM64 (most modern devices)
#   zig build -Dtarget=arm-linux-androideabi         # ARMv7 (older devices)
#   zig build -Dtarget=x86_64-linux-android          # x86_64 emulator
#
# The build will automatically enter "libs-only" mode for mobile targets,
# building only static libraries for integration into native Android apps.

# Android NDK path (optional - Zig has built-in cross-compilation support)
# ANDROID_NDK_PATH=/path/to/android-ndk-r26b

# Minimum Android API level (default: 21 = Android 5.0 Lollipop)
# Set via: zig build -Dandroid-api=21
# Supported values: 21 (Lollipop), 24 (Nougat), 26 (Oreo), etc.

# Note: DXC is NOT required for Android builds
# Shaders should be pre-compiled to SPIRV at build time on desktop

# Vulkan SDK path (only needed if building Vulkan shaders)
# VULKAN_SDK_PATH=/path/to/vulkan-sdk

# =============================================================================
# Integration Guide for Android Projects
# =============================================================================
#
# After building with zig build -Dtarget=aarch64-linux-android:
#
# 1. Static libraries will be in: zig-out/lib/
#    - libquickjs.a
#    - liblexbor_static.a
#    - libyogacore.a
#    - libfreetype.a
#    - libharfbuzz.a
#    - libmsdfgen.a
#
# 2. Copy these to your Android project:
#    app/src/main/jniLibs/arm64-v8a/
#
# 3. In your CMakeLists.txt or Android.mk, link against these libraries
#
# 4. Header files are in: zig-out/include/
#    Copy to: app/src/main/cpp/include/
#
# =============================================================================
